Common viva questions
1. What is JavaScript?
JavaScript is a scripting language used to make web pages interactive.
2. Why is parseFloat() used?
It converts input into numbers.
3. What is switch used for?
It selects one block of code from multiple choices.
4. Why are functions used?
Functions make code simple, reusable, and organized.
5. What does getElementById() do?
It selects an HTML element by id.
6. What does innerHTML do?
It changes or displays content inside an HTML element.
